WEBVTT

1
00:00:21.605 --> 00:00:23.107
[DOOR LOCK BEEPS THEN BUZZES]

2
00:00:34.201 --> 00:00:36.374
Hey. Pete. You have a good one.

3
00:00:36.537 --> 00:00:37.584
Uh-huh.

4
00:00:45.796 --> 00:00:47.298
[ENGINE REVS]

5
00:00:47.464 --> 00:00:49.466
[MUSIC PLAYING OVER CAR SPEAKERS]

6
00:00:52.302 --> 00:00:53.770
MAN:
See you tomorrow. Pete.

7
00:00:54.763 --> 00:00:56.185
Where is everybody?

8
00:01:01.645 --> 00:01:03.238
Gene?

9
00:01:06.066 --> 00:01:08.034
OFFICER:
Oh. my God.

10
00:01:08.902 --> 00:01:12.031
Call it in! Signal 63!
Get some help. now!

11
00:01:19.621 --> 00:01:21.623
[ALARM WAILING]

12
00:01:43.854 --> 00:01:45.856
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

13
00:01:55.907 --> 00:01:57.329
[SIGHS]

14
00:01:59.536 --> 00:02:01.538
[CLEARS THROAT]

15
00:02:12.049 --> 00:02:13.175
[KEYPAD BEEPS]

16
00:02:28.398 --> 00:02:30.651
WOMAN [ON TV]:
<i>--where he was a professor of literature.</i>

17
00:02:30.817 --> 00:02:35.618
<i>So far. five guards are confirmed dead
from this prison escape.</i>

18
00:02:35.781 --> 00:02:37.499
MAN [ON TV]:
<i>--prison early this morning.</i>

19
00:02:37.658 --> 00:02:40.411
<i>As you may recall.
Carroll was convicted in 2004...</i>

20
00:02:40.577 --> 00:02:43.205
<i>...!'or the murders of 14 young women...</i>

21
00:02:43.372 --> 00:02:44.794
<i>attended the university...</i>

22
00:02:44.956 --> 00:02:47.004
[CELL PHONE RINGS]
<i>...where he was a professor of literature.</i>

23
00:02:47.167 --> 00:02:48.214
Hello?

24
00:02:48.377 --> 00:02:50.505
FRANKLIN [OVER PHONE]:
<i>Hello. Ryan. it's Director Franklin. FBI.</i>

25
00:02:50.671 --> 00:02:53.094
<i>- It's been</i> a <i>while.
- Yeah.</i>

26
00:02:53.256 --> 00:02:55.008
What can I do for you. sir?

27
00:02:55.175 --> 00:02:57.769
<i>FRANKLIN:
We need you in Virginia. Ryan.</i>

28
00:02:58.470 --> 00:02:59.813
I'm not an agent anymore.

29
00:02:59.971 --> 00:03:03.692
<i>I know things didn't end well
with the Bureau. but you caught Carroll.</i>

30
00:03:03.850 --> 00:03:05.318
<i>No one knows him like you m.</i>

31
00:03:05.477 --> 00:03:07.696
<i>I've got good agents on ii.</i>

32
00:03:07.938 --> 00:03:12.694
<i>Go consult. educate them.
We have to find him fast.</i>

33
00:03:12.859 --> 00:03:16.784
<i>MAN [ON TV]: So far. five guards are
confirmed dead from the prison escape.</i>

34
00:03:16.947 --> 00:03:19.041
<i>Joe Carroll is still at large.</i>

35
00:03:19.366 --> 00:03:21.289
FRANKLIN [OVER PHONE]:
<i>Will you do it. Ryan?</i>

36
00:03:45.142 --> 00:03:47.110
[SIREN WAILING]

37
00:03:47.269 --> 00:03:49.192
[TIRES SCREECH]

38
00:03:52.149 --> 00:03:54.026
Sarah Fuller?

39
00:03:55.235 --> 00:03:59.706
Detective Warren. Norfolk P.D.
We're on behalf of the U.S. Marshals Office.

40
00:03:59.865 --> 00:04:01.742
Okay.

41
00:04:02.325 --> 00:04:03.497
What's going on?

42
00:04:03.660 --> 00:04:07.631
Joe Carroll. He escaped from prison
earlier this morning.

43
00:04:08.665 --> 00:04:11.009
I'm sorry. he what?

44
00:04:13.503 --> 00:04:15.505
WOMAN:
And where was the knife at this point'?

45
00:04:15.672 --> 00:04:19.643
The knife that was used
to stab you repeatedly.

46
00:04:22.095 --> 00:04:23.938
It was still inside me.

47
00:04:25.015 --> 00:04:27.814
I reached down to pull it out.
but I was too weak.

48
00:04:27.976 --> 00:04:29.728
WOMAN:
So. what did you do?

49
00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:32.943
I pushed it. instead...

50
00:04:33.106 --> 00:04:35.859
...deeper into my stomach and to the right.

51
00:04:36.026 --> 00:04:37.278
Why would you do that?

52
00:04:41.615 --> 00:04:47.622
To puncture the splenic artery.
to bleed out faster.

53
00:04:47.788 --> 00:04:51.088
I just wanted it to be over.

54
00:04:52.626 --> 00:04:55.971
WARREN: I'll have men in place both inside
and out. Strictly precautionary.

55
00:04:56.129 --> 00:04:57.301
We're gonna keep you safe.

56
00:04:57.464 --> 00:05:00.217
MAN: Whoa. can't let you in.
WILL: I'm her neighbor. Will Wilson.

57
00:05:00.383 --> 00:05:02.010
He's okay.

58
00:05:02.177 --> 00:05:03.554
WILL:
Sarah.

59
00:05:04.054 --> 00:05:06.307
I saw the news. It's all over TV.

60
00:05:06.473 --> 00:05:11.479
Billy's on his way home. We're here for you.
Whatever you need.

61
00:05:11.645 --> 00:05:13.613
[WHIMPERING]
I'm so glad you're here.

62
00:05:34.209 --> 00:05:37.429
TROY:
Ryan Hardy. I'm Agent Troy Riley. BAU2.

63
00:05:37.587 --> 00:05:38.964
This is Agent Jennifer Mason.

64
00:05:39.130 --> 00:05:40.382
JENNIFER:
Thank you for coming.

65
00:05:40.549 --> 00:05:42.017
Not sure what Franklin told you.

66
00:05:42.175 --> 00:05:45.224
Marshals are heading the search.
We're running point for the Bureau.

67
00:05:45.387 --> 00:05:46.434
Command center set up in town.

68
00:05:46.596 --> 00:05:48.598
JENNIFER:
Your being here may raise eyebrows.

69
00:05:48.765 --> 00:05:49.982
That book you wrote.

70
00:05:50.141 --> 00:05:51.518
Not to mention my reputation.

71
00:05:51.685 --> 00:05:52.937
We'll do the talking.

72
00:05:53.103 --> 00:05:56.232
If anyone asks. you're here
strictly as a consultant. Questions?

73
00:05:56.398 --> 00:05:58.696
Yeah. How's Sarah Fuller'?

74
00:05:59.526 --> 00:06:02.279
Carroll's last victim.
She's a doctor now in Norfolk.

75
00:06:02.445 --> 00:06:04.493
- Is she safe?
- Yes. She's under 24/7 watch.

76
00:06:04.656 --> 00:06:06.704
- I'd like to speak to her.
JENNIFER: About what?

77
00:06:07.409 --> 00:06:09.082
I'd like to know how she's doing.

78
00:06:09.911 --> 00:06:12.915
Perhaps later
when we're not trying to find a serial killer.

79
00:06:13.081 --> 00:06:16.927
TURNER:
He kills all of them in under two minutes.

80
00:06:17.085 --> 00:06:18.507
There he goes.

81
00:06:27.470 --> 00:06:28.517
[RYAN SIGHS]

82
00:06:28.680 --> 00:06:31.229
Ryan Hardy.
this is Deputy Marshal Scott Turner.

83
00:06:31.391 --> 00:06:34.770
I know Ryan. I was with the sheriffs office
when he brought Carroll in.

84
00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:36.692
Scott.

85
00:06:36.855 --> 00:06:39.404
Director Franklin asked Mr. Hardy
to consult.

86
00:06:39.566 --> 00:06:41.159
Then he's your problem. Agent.

87
00:06:48.366 --> 00:06:49.788
He left it like this.

88
00:06:52.287 --> 00:06:56.588
Forensics swept. Nothing.
He's scheduled to be executed next month.

89
00:06:56.750 --> 00:06:58.377
The twelfth.

90
00:07:00.253 --> 00:07:02.301
Still the romantic.

91
00:07:06.301 --> 00:07:07.348
[SIGHS]

92
00:07:11.056 --> 00:07:12.353
Who let him have this?

93
00:07:12.515 --> 00:07:14.062
JENNIFER:
Anyone could have.

94
00:07:16.728 --> 00:07:18.696
"Dear Ryan. I enjoyed your book.

95
00:07:18.855 --> 00:07:21.699
Have you ever considered a sequel?
Best. Joe."

96
00:07:21.858 --> 00:07:23.531
You never mentioned a note.

97
00:07:23.693 --> 00:07:27.948
- Any idea why he left that for you?
- He enjoyed my book. Said so.

98
00:07:28.114 --> 00:07:31.163
- He's letting us know he plans to kill again.
- That's probably it.

99
00:07:31.326 --> 00:07:34.205
Look. I read your file.
I know you don't play well with others.

100
00:07:34.371 --> 00:07:38.126
You read my file? So you know me.
is that what it is?

101
00:07:38.291 --> 00:07:39.964
Forget it.

102
00:07:40.919 --> 00:07:45.641
Claire Matthews. Carroll's ex-wife.
Has anyone been in touch with her?

103
00:07:45.799 --> 00:07:47.597
She's being questioned.

104
00:07:48.051 --> 00:07:50.975
We have her under protection as well.

105
00:07:53.348 --> 00:07:55.350
[PEOPLE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

106
00:08:05.527 --> 00:08:08.827
Sorry for the intrusion. Ms. Matthews.
I have a few questions.

107
00:08:09.155 --> 00:08:11.658
When was the last time
your husband contacted you?

108
00:08:11.825 --> 00:08:14.578
Ex-husband.
And I don't mean to be rude. detective...

109
00:08:14.744 --> 00:08:16.997
...but I'm gonna wait for the FBI to arrive.

110
00:08:17.664 --> 00:08:20.008
And I need to speak to Ryan Hardy.

111
00:08:22.335 --> 00:08:23.928
Thank you.

112
00:08:36.933 --> 00:08:38.059
[GASPS]

113
00:08:38.226 --> 00:08:39.273
[BOTH CHUCKLES]

114
00:08:39.436 --> 00:08:42.064
So how did it go?

115
00:08:42.230 --> 00:08:43.698
It's official. I'm pregnant.

116
00:08:43.857 --> 00:08:45.154
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

117
00:08:48.236 --> 00:08:50.284
JOEY:
Mom? Mom?

118
00:08:50.697 --> 00:08:53.416
- Yeah. honey.
JOEY: What's going on?

119
00:08:54.117 --> 00:08:55.539
Why can't I watch TV?

120
00:08:56.536 --> 00:08:59.915
- I didn't know what to say.
- Um...

121
00:09:00.081 --> 00:09:02.175
It's Dad. isn't it?

122
00:09:02.667 --> 00:09:04.510
Oh. honey.

123
00:09:14.137 --> 00:09:16.731
I need to speak to someone
about Joe Carroll?

124
00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:19.860
Fill this out.
Take a seat with the others.

125
00:09:23.855 --> 00:09:25.607
WESTON:
He studied in the States...

126
00:09:25.774 --> 00:09:28.197
...married and became a professor
at Winslow University.

127
00:09:28.359 --> 00:09:29.781
Also. a budding novelist.

128
00:09:29.944 --> 00:09:32.197
In 2003. Carroll's first and only novel...

129
00:09:32.363 --> 00:09:35.537
...The <i>Gothic Sea.</i> was published.
It became a best-seller...

130
00:09:35.700 --> 00:09:39.330
...but in its initial printing.
it was a commercial and critical flop.

131
00:09:39.871 --> 00:09:44.297
This triggered his piquerism. the act
of stabbing. slicing ﬂesh for arousal--

132
00:09:44.459 --> 00:09:45.836
RYAN:
That's not accurate.

133
00:09:46.836 --> 00:09:49.180
I'm sorry.
would you like to say something. sir?

134
00:09:51.466 --> 00:09:54.310
By all means. if I've got it wrong.
please correct me.

135
00:09:55.095 --> 00:09:56.893
Ryan Hardy.

136
00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:04.734
Joe Carroll was obsessed
with the Romantic Period.

137
00:10:04.896 --> 00:10:09.322
His lectures
consisted of Thoreau. Emerson...

138
00:10:09.526 --> 00:10:11.745
...in particular. his hero. Edgar Allan Poe.

139
00:10:11.903 --> 00:10:14.702
Like Poe. he believed in the insanity of art.

140
00:10:14.864 --> 00:10:18.334
That it had to be felt.

141
00:10:18.827 --> 00:10:22.172
He didn't just eviscerate
14 female students...

142
00:10:23.665 --> 00:10:25.667
...he was making art.

143
00:10:25.834 --> 00:10:29.008
He cut out his victim's eyes
as a nod to his favorite works of Poe:

144
00:10:29.170 --> 00:10:31.138
"The Tell-Tale Heart" and "The Black Cat."

145
00:10:31.548 --> 00:10:36.896
Poe believed that the eyes are our identity.
windows to our soul.

146
00:10:37.053 --> 00:10:41.729
To classify him as a piquerist
would be too simplistic.

147
00:10:46.896 --> 00:10:49.024
WESTON:
Okay. guys. Thanks.

148
00:10:53.486 --> 00:10:55.989
Mike Weston. ifs a real honor. sir.

149
00:10:56.281 --> 00:10:58.375
I did my thesis on Joe Carroll
at the Academy.

150
00:10:58.533 --> 00:11:01.787
Your book was. heh. invaluable.
It's a real thrill for me. sir.

151
00:11:01.953 --> 00:11:03.455
JENNIFER:
Hardy.

152
00:11:06.207 --> 00:11:08.460
Wow. heh. that was pathetic.

153
00:11:08.626 --> 00:11:10.970
The man is a hero.
Took down Carroll single-handed.

154
00:11:11.129 --> 00:11:12.881
And the Bureau still let him go.

155
00:11:13.047 --> 00:11:15.675
You haven't read his book. have you?
He's on disability.

156
00:11:15.842 --> 00:11:17.469
Turner said he lost it. went crazy.

157
00:11:17.635 --> 00:11:20.639
Carroll stabbed him in the chest.
punctured his left ventricular.

158
00:11:20.805 --> 00:11:23.854
He can't be in the field.
Got a pacemaker keeping it all pumping.

159
00:11:29.981 --> 00:11:31.779
Who are the women?

160
00:11:32.025 --> 00:11:35.495
Carroll's groupies. We're interviewing
anyone who visited him in prison.

161
00:11:35.653 --> 00:11:37.872
Carroll had 112 visitors
in the last two years.

162
00:11:38.031 --> 00:11:41.786
Forty-three in the last six months.
Fourteen visited over four times.

163
00:11:41.951 --> 00:11:43.168
Who had the most access?

164
00:11:43.369 --> 00:11:45.542
Was he confined to his cell?
Any privileges?

165
00:11:45.705 --> 00:11:47.958
Spent most of his time
preparing for his appeal.

166
00:11:48.124 --> 00:11:49.967
Forgone legal aid.
representing himself.

167
00:11:50.335 --> 00:11:52.554
- His records.
- He had access to a legal library?

168
00:11:52.712 --> 00:11:55.181
Every Tuesday.
Carroll was shackled and transported...

169
00:11:55.340 --> 00:11:58.765
...to the Sussex County Law Library.
Confined to a sealed room. one guard.

170
00:11:58.927 --> 00:12:01.851
- And furnished with law books.
- Actual books or digital files?

171
00:12:02.013 --> 00:12:04.607
Digital. Everything's archived
on the library's server.

172
00:12:04.766 --> 00:12:07.360
- He had Internet access?
-It would have been restricted.

173
00:12:07.518 --> 00:12:09.691
Because that would stop Joe Carroll.

174
00:12:11.689 --> 00:12:15.239
- We need to rip apart the library's Ethernet.
- Get the cyber techs.

175
00:12:44.639 --> 00:12:45.686
[ALL SCREAMING]

176
00:12:45.848 --> 00:12:47.225
WOMAN: No!
- Stand back!

177
00:12:48.268 --> 00:12:50.441
Take it easy. ma'am.
easy. easy!

178
00:12:51.479 --> 00:12:54.904
Drop the weapon!
Drop the weapon! Drop it!

179
00:12:55.358 --> 00:12:58.157
Ma'am. ma'am. Look at me. look at me.

180
00:12:58.319 --> 00:13:00.162
You don't wanna do this.

181
00:13:00.446 --> 00:13:01.993
Okay?

182
00:13:03.032 --> 00:13:07.003
Just hand that thing to me.
And everything's gonna be okay.

183
00:13:07.161 --> 00:13:10.085
-"Lord. help my poor soul."
- No.

184
00:13:10.248 --> 00:13:14.594
-"Lord. help my poor soul."
- No. no.

185
00:13:14.752 --> 00:13:16.629
[ALL SCREAMING]

186
00:13:19.299 --> 00:13:21.222
[GASPING]

187
00:13:26.931 --> 00:13:30.401
She's right-handed. She did
most of the upper-left region herself.

188
00:13:30.560 --> 00:13:34.781
But this is someone else. Carroll. possibly.

189
00:13:34.939 --> 00:13:37.909
- We're running analysis for a match.
- Thank you.

190
00:13:41.029 --> 00:13:43.031
<i>Once upon a midnight dreary</i>

191
00:13:43.197 --> 00:13:44.699
"The Raven."

192
00:13:52.707 --> 00:13:54.926
<i>This fever called "Living"
is conquered at last.</i>

193
00:13:55.084 --> 00:13:56.131
It's all Poe.

194
00:13:56.294 --> 00:13:58.592
- And what she said at the end--
- Poe's last words.

195
00:13:59.047 --> 00:14:02.142
When found delirious on the streets.
he's believed to have uttered:

196
00:14:02.300 --> 00:14:03.677
"Lord. help my poor soul."

197
00:14:07.513 --> 00:14:10.232
- Is that water. sin'?
- Yes.

198
00:14:11.351 --> 00:14:12.568
Mint?

199
00:14:13.353 --> 00:14:14.696
Sure.

200
00:14:17.315 --> 00:14:20.569
We've run her prints.
So far. we've found seven identities.

201
00:14:20.735 --> 00:14:24.581
Four are wanted in three states.
Two visited Carroll in the last six months.

202
00:14:24.739 --> 00:14:26.958
- Anything on the cell phone?
Disposable.

203
00:14:27.116 --> 00:14:28.459
The text said. "Do it now."

204
00:14:28.618 --> 00:14:32.213
Carroll could easily convince an unbalanced
brain to do this. exertion of power. theatrics.

205
00:14:32.372 --> 00:14:33.419
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

206
00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:37.673
I have Sarah Fuller for you.

207
00:14:40.296 --> 00:14:45.268
- Hello?
- Mr. Hardy. It's been a long time.

208
00:14:46.511 --> 00:14:49.685
Sarah. Hi. how are you doing?

209
00:14:49.847 --> 00:14:52.566
Well. not great. heh.

210
00:14:53.309 --> 00:14:54.356
[SIGHS]

211
00:14:54.519 --> 00:14:56.988
Listen. we're going to find him.

212
00:14:57.146 --> 00:15:00.616
Nothing's going to happen to you.
I promise you that.

213
00:15:03.027 --> 00:15:04.745
I really appreciate you calling.

214
00:15:05.321 --> 00:15:10.873
I'm just. uh. happy to hear you're safe.

215
00:15:12.203 --> 00:15:13.830
Bye-bye. now.

216
00:15:13.996 --> 00:15:15.748
Bye. Mr. Hardy.

217
00:15:27.385 --> 00:15:31.060
- Thank you.
- They questioned Claire Matthews.

218
00:15:31.222 --> 00:15:33.691
She won't speak to anyone but you.
Why is that?

219
00:15:34.517 --> 00:15:36.485
When I speak to her. I'll ask her.

220
00:15:39.355 --> 00:15:40.902
Thanks.

221
00:15:41.065 --> 00:15:42.942
I don't think you got enough food. babe.

222
00:15:43.109 --> 00:15:46.659
Do we really have to feed the cops?
Can't they just order pizza?

223
00:15:46.821 --> 00:15:49.791
There's plenty of food.
Thank you. Billy.

224
00:15:52.326 --> 00:15:56.422
- How's she doing?
- She's right here. She's fine.

225
00:15:56.581 --> 00:16:00.211
Then why are we ignoring that hot cop
in the corner over there?

226
00:16:00.376 --> 00:16:04.381
- Is he single?
- He's not wearing a ring. I checked.

227
00:16:05.339 --> 00:16:07.683
MAN <i>[ON</i> TV]:
<i>And with his charm and good looks...</i>

228
00:16:07.842 --> 00:16:12.643
<i>...he was understandably</i> a <i>favorite
amongst the female contingent.</i>

229
00:16:12.805 --> 00:16:17.026
Poe's chief principle. Insanity as art.

230
00:16:17.351 --> 00:16:18.898
This is the Romantic Period.

231
00:16:19.061 --> 00:16:23.237
Death is about theme.
mood. motif. emotional aesthetic.

232
00:16:23.399 --> 00:16:25.822
Poe equates death with what?

233
00:16:25.985 --> 00:16:30.161
- He equates death with love?
- No. not love. Poe equates death with--

234
00:16:30.323 --> 00:16:34.294
Beauty?
Poe believed that an was about beauty...

235
00:16:34.452 --> 00:16:38.082
...and that nothing was more beautiful
than the death of a beautiful woman.

236
00:16:38.247 --> 00:16:40.716
Helen. Lenore. Annabel Lee.

237
00:16:40.875 --> 00:16:43.003
"To bereave beauty is...

238
00:16:43.169 --> 00:16:46.924
...to elevate one's soul."

239
00:16:51.594 --> 00:16:53.938
Carroll never visited
the same web address twice...

240
00:16:54.096 --> 00:16:56.815
-...which suggests he's using various URLs.
- Who with?

241
00:16:56.974 --> 00:17:00.444
Every time I access an IP address.
it mutates. it's a sophisticated virus.

242
00:17:00.603 --> 00:17:04.107
Where were the guards when he was
chatting online? Who are these idiots?

243
00:17:04.273 --> 00:17:08.244
The detail changed. but there's one
recurring name: Jordan Raines.

244
00:17:08.402 --> 00:17:12.908
Jordan "Jordy" Raines. 32.
four-year employee...

245
00:17:13.074 --> 00:17:14.792
...death row. works the night shift--

246
00:17:14.951 --> 00:17:16.578
- Was he working last night?
RYAN: Uh...

247
00:17:16.744 --> 00:17:19.247
Called in sick. That's him.

248
00:17:19.413 --> 00:17:20.915
- Prison guard.
- Helped Carroll escape.

249
00:17:21.082 --> 00:17:23.050
- Get his home address.
- Yeah. I got it.

250
00:17:25.545 --> 00:17:27.092
[TIRES SCREECH]

251
00:17:38.057 --> 00:17:40.606
Federal agents. Open up.

252
00:17:40.768 --> 00:17:42.395
Hit it.

253
00:17:44.772 --> 00:17:46.866
MAN 1: Clear the room!
MAN 2: Room clear.

254
00:17:47.024 --> 00:17:48.697
MAN 1:
All clear.

255
00:17:49.026 --> 00:17:50.824
He's not here.

256
00:18:00.746 --> 00:18:04.922
JORDY [ON COMPUTER]:
Hi. <i>Hi.</i> Say hi to the camera.

257
00:18:05.084 --> 00:18:06.552
WESTON:
Guys.

258
00:18:07.128 --> 00:18:08.425
JORDY:
Say hi.

259
00:18:10.423 --> 00:18:12.596
<i>Say hi.
“Hi.”.</i>

260
00:18:13.092 --> 00:18:17.563
<i>Your friends are out there.
That's right. buddy. Sweet pup.</i>

261
00:18:18.306 --> 00:18:20.650
You're gonna want to see this.

262
00:18:23.144 --> 00:18:24.316
[RYAN GAGS]

263
00:18:41.287 --> 00:18:42.584
WESTON:
What is that?

264
00:18:43.748 --> 00:18:45.341
RYAN:
It's a German Shepherd. I think.

265
00:18:48.419 --> 00:18:49.716
[GROWLS]

266
00:18:49.879 --> 00:18:51.631
[ALL GASP]

267
00:18:51.797 --> 00:18:53.014
[YELPS]

268
00:18:53.924 --> 00:18:56.427
Carroll is teaching him
how to become a serial killer.

269
00:18:57.303 --> 00:18:58.930
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

270
00:19:04.560 --> 00:19:08.781
I can handle dead people.
But you kill a dog. I go crazy.

271
00:19:09.649 --> 00:19:13.745
I got this little terrier mix--
Forget it.

272
00:19:17.573 --> 00:19:19.575
- What is that?
- Joe Carroll's novel.

273
00:19:19.742 --> 00:19:21.335
Oh. look. it's inscribed.

274
00:19:21.494 --> 00:19:25.374
"Jordy. you're capable of greatness.
You just have to believe. Joe."

275
00:19:25.539 --> 00:19:29.169
So this Jordy guy is lonely. unstable.
vulnerable lo kindness.

276
00:19:29.335 --> 00:19:31.963
Carroll recognizes his potential
and seduces him.

277
00:19:32.129 --> 00:19:35.349
He's emulating Carroll.
The animals. he removed their eyes.

278
00:19:35.508 --> 00:19:37.886
Jordy looks to Carroll
the way Carroll looks to Poe.

279
00:19:38.052 --> 00:19:40.851
- It's a godlike worship.
-ls Carroll really that powerful?

280
00:19:41.013 --> 00:19:44.392
When I first started to suspect him.
all I had was instinct.

281
00:19:44.558 --> 00:19:46.310
I didn't have any evidence at all.

282
00:19:46.477 --> 00:19:50.232
I was having a hard time convincing people
of my Poe theory.

283
00:19:50.398 --> 00:19:52.742
In the book.
that's when you started following him.

284
00:19:52.900 --> 00:19:56.905
- Yeah. everywhere. Home. Work. School.
- Yeah.

285
00:19:57.071 --> 00:20:01.167
I was waiting for him to get sloppy.
That's when I first recognized Sarah Fuller.

286
00:20:01.325 --> 00:20:04.875
I'd seen her in his class.
I used to sit there and watch him teach.

287
00:20:05.037 --> 00:20:07.335
He was amazing.

288
00:20:07.498 --> 00:20:11.253
He could inspire people. That's a gift.

289
00:20:12.753 --> 00:20:14.847
Hardy. let's go.

290
00:20:15.005 --> 00:20:17.884
- Where to?
-It's time you talked to Claire Matthews.

291
00:20:18.050 --> 00:20:19.768
FEMALE [ON TV]:
<i>No official word at this time...</i>

292
00:20:19.927 --> 00:20:24.478
<i>"but sources have confirmed that a woman
is dead today) by her own hands.</i>

293
00:20:24.640 --> 00:20:27.359
<i>Now the FBI is speculating the victim
may have been...</i>

294
00:20:27.518 --> 00:20:30.738
<i>-...one of Joe Carroll's groupies--
- Enough</i> of <i>that.</i>

295
00:20:31.689 --> 00:20:33.282
I say we watch a movie.

296
00:20:33.983 --> 00:20:37.203
I think I'm gonna lay down for a bit.
If ifs okay with you guys'?

297
00:20:37.361 --> 00:20:39.534
- Yeah.
- That's even a better idea.

298
00:20:39.697 --> 00:20:41.665
You should get some rest.

299
00:20:44.660 --> 00:20:46.458
We're right next door. okay?

300
00:20:46.620 --> 00:20:49.669
- You call us if you need anything.
- We'll come running.

301
00:20:49.832 --> 00:20:51.129
I love you guys.

302
00:20:51.292 --> 00:20:53.511
We love you. Good night.

303
00:21:21.447 --> 00:21:23.870
SARAH: You want me to have manners.
That was creepy.

304
00:21:24.033 --> 00:21:27.162
ANNIE: The whole night's been creepy.
SARAH: Yeah.

305
00:21:28.954 --> 00:21:30.672
SARAH:
It's so quiet.

306
00:21:30.831 --> 00:21:35.712
Because everyone's in Daytona.
Having fun. Everyone but us.

307
00:21:38.923 --> 00:21:39.970
[FAUCET RUNNING]

308
00:21:40.132 --> 00:21:43.511
ANNIE: The hangover has begun.
- I told you not to drink.

309
00:21:43.677 --> 00:21:46.180
I'm not interesting enough to not drink.
That's you--

310
00:21:48.098 --> 00:21:49.145
You Okay?

311
00:21:49.308 --> 00:21:50.685
[FAUCET STOPS]

312
00:21:54.063 --> 00:21:55.736
Annie?

313
00:22:07.493 --> 00:22:09.291
Annie?

314
00:22:17.002 --> 00:22:18.049
[SCREAMS]

315
00:22:26.220 --> 00:22:27.267
[GASPS]

316
00:22:27.555 --> 00:22:28.681
WARREN:
Sorry.

317
00:22:28.848 --> 00:22:32.443
Just to let you know. there's two officers
outside the door If you need them.

318
00:22:33.978 --> 00:22:35.571
Sure. Thank you.

319
00:22:44.530 --> 00:22:46.532
Claire will be right down.

320
00:22:46.782 --> 00:22:49.706
- Hey. Joey.
- Do I know you?

321
00:22:49.869 --> 00:22:52.418
Yeah. but I haven't seen you
since you were this big.

322
00:22:52.580 --> 00:22:53.957
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

323
00:22:55.291 --> 00:22:57.419
Let's let the man do his job.

324
00:23:05.301 --> 00:23:06.723
Professor Matthews?

325
00:23:07.386 --> 00:23:08.979
- Yes?
- Hi.

326
00:23:10.222 --> 00:23:14.477
I'm Agent Ryan Hardy with the FBI.
Can I speak with you?

327
00:23:15.477 --> 00:23:17.320
Sure.

328
00:23:17.479 --> 00:23:20.323
- I didn't know about the eyes.
-It was withheld.

329
00:23:21.191 --> 00:23:23.364
Try Edgar Allan Poe.

330
00:23:23.986 --> 00:23:27.661
Um. "The Tell-Tale Heart." "The Black Cat."
Both have strong eye allegories.

331
00:23:27.865 --> 00:23:30.709
The eyes are symbolic.
The essence of identity.

332
00:23:31.994 --> 00:23:35.464
You should talk to my husband.
He knows a lot about that time period.

333
00:23:35.831 --> 00:23:38.801
- You're married?
- Yes. heh. I'm married. Agent Hardy.

334
00:23:38.959 --> 00:23:41.553
Why? Were you flirting?

335
00:23:42.922 --> 00:23:44.924
[BOTH LAUGH]

336
00:23:45.841 --> 00:23:48.890
With this material? No. not a chance.

337
00:23:55.517 --> 00:23:57.770
- Hello. Ryan.
- Claire.

338
00:23:58.479 --> 00:24:01.904
I'm Agent Mason. Ms. Matthews.
You wanted to speak to Mr. Hardy.

339
00:24:02.066 --> 00:24:04.319
Yes. but I need to speak with him alone.

340
00:24:04.485 --> 00:24:06.203
I'm afraid that's not possible.

341
00:24:06.362 --> 00:24:08.490
I'm afraid I have to insist.

342
00:24:13.285 --> 00:24:15.208
Would you excuse us for a minute?

343
00:24:19.458 --> 00:24:20.505
How's your heart?

344
00:24:21.377 --> 00:24:22.469
Same.

345
00:24:23.462 --> 00:24:25.385
But you're drinking too much.

346
00:24:28.884 --> 00:24:30.807
- Have you heard from him?
- Yeah.

347
00:24:31.345 --> 00:24:32.892
Uh. a week ago. This came for me.

348
00:24:33.055 --> 00:24:35.274
I thought you should see it.

349
00:24:39.853 --> 00:24:41.150
How does he know?

350
00:24:42.898 --> 00:24:44.400
He doesn't. He's guessing.

351
00:24:44.566 --> 00:24:47.410
No one needs to know about this.
Not gonna help us find him.

352
00:24:49.363 --> 00:24:50.956
We have two killers out there now.

353
00:24:52.241 --> 00:24:53.288
He's got help.

354
00:24:53.450 --> 00:24:54.918
[SIGHS]

355
00:24:59.581 --> 00:25:00.924
Are you a COP?

356
00:25:05.379 --> 00:25:06.756
Joe's always teaching.

357
00:25:06.922 --> 00:25:10.392
It was ingrained in him
so it makes sense he would find a student.

358
00:25:10.551 --> 00:25:13.475
Where do you think they would go?
Would he leave the country?

359
00:25:13.637 --> 00:25:15.389
No. Joe's not looking for his freedom.

360
00:25:15.556 --> 00:25:18.560
- He wants to keep killing.
- He's good at it.

361
00:25:19.268 --> 00:25:21.236
I need to find him. Claire.

362
00:25:21.395 --> 00:25:23.489
And I don't think I know how.

363
00:25:32.072 --> 00:25:33.995
I'm sorry I didn't call you.

364
00:25:36.118 --> 00:25:38.212
It's been eight years. Ryan.
I got the hint.

365
00:25:40.289 --> 00:25:44.760
I know when the FBI found out about us.
that was difficult for you.

366
00:25:44.918 --> 00:25:48.548
No. That's not why I didn't call.

367
00:25:49.381 --> 00:25:50.974
You deserve more.

368
00:25:51.425 --> 00:25:52.972
I belong in your past.

369
00:25:53.927 --> 00:25:56.271
I work better in people's pasts.
I always have.

370
00:26:05.689 --> 00:26:06.781
Uh...

371
00:26:06.940 --> 00:26:10.035
The girl is safe? The last victim? She's--?

372
00:26:10.194 --> 00:26:14.540
Sarah Fuller. Uh. yes.
She's under protection.

373
00:26:14.698 --> 00:26:16.416
She's good. She's a doctor now. heh.

374
00:26:16.575 --> 00:26:19.545
I'm glad someone
<i>was</i> able to get beyond this.

375
00:26:19.703 --> 00:26:21.626
I'm sure that upsets Joe.

376
00:26:22.039 --> 00:26:23.336
Why is that?

377
00:26:23.499 --> 00:26:27.174
Heh. he fancies himself Edgar Allan Poe.
That was the impetus for writing his novel.

378
00:26:27.336 --> 00:26:30.260
Poe died with an unfinished manuscript.
"The Light-House."

379
00:26:30.422 --> 00:26:34.552
Joe's novel. The Gothic Sea.
was his way of finishing what Poe started.

380
00:26:37.513 --> 00:26:39.265
- What was that about?
-It was personal.

381
00:26:39.431 --> 00:26:40.808
What do you mean. "personal"?

382
00:26:40.974 --> 00:26:43.477
- We have to get to Sarah Fuller.
- What did she tell you?

383
00:26:43.644 --> 00:26:46.989
Carroll's gonna make a move.
To finish what he started: Sarah.

384
00:26:57.574 --> 00:26:59.372
It's right this way.

385
00:27:01.411 --> 00:27:02.754
I'm Detective Warren.

386
00:27:02.913 --> 00:27:04.836
Miss Fuller went to bed about an hour ago.

387
00:27:04.998 --> 00:27:06.671
Officer Pontz works the front door.

388
00:27:08.919 --> 00:27:10.717
Other officer here.

389
00:27:10.879 --> 00:27:12.256
Two men up the stairs.

390
00:27:12.422 --> 00:27:14.800
WARREN: Officers?
JENNIFER: Where are they?

391
00:27:14.967 --> 00:27:17.811
Officer Watts? Kelly?

392
00:27:17.970 --> 00:27:20.723
Where are you guys?
They should be here.

393
00:27:22.558 --> 00:27:24.356
Sarah?

394
00:27:25.686 --> 00:27:28.360
She's gone. Where is she?
Where the hell is she?

395
00:27:28.522 --> 00:27:29.865
- I don't know.
- How'd she get out'?

396
00:27:30.023 --> 00:27:31.900
We got an officer down!

397
00:27:34.236 --> 00:27:35.704
OFFICER:
Move! Move!

398
00:27:51.211 --> 00:27:54.806
- Go around.
WARREN: Neighbors next door. Let's go.

399
00:27:58.719 --> 00:28:00.266
[WHISPERS]
Give me a light.

400
00:29:15.879 --> 00:29:17.677
[DOOR BANGS]

401
00:29:33.689 --> 00:29:35.066
[SIGHS]

402
00:29:37.442 --> 00:29:40.195
Get the lights. Get the lights!

403
00:29:46.410 --> 00:29:47.753
Hardy.

404
00:30:06.430 --> 00:30:08.603
The neighbors.
Will Wilson and Billy Thomas...

405
00:30:08.765 --> 00:30:10.608
...left in their SUE? 40 minutes ago.

406
00:30:10.767 --> 00:30:12.485
RYAN:
No one thought to search the vehicle?

407
00:30:12.644 --> 00:30:14.897
There was no reason to check.
She wasn't missing.

408
00:30:15.063 --> 00:30:17.111
Will Wilson teaches public school.
2nd grade.

409
00:30:17.274 --> 00:30:20.494
Billy Thomas is a computer tech.
He runs the fraud division of a bank.

410
00:30:20.652 --> 00:30:22.404
I bet they weren't gay either.

411
00:30:22.571 --> 00:30:26.292
Carroll placed them hereto watch over her
until he was ready.

412
00:30:26.450 --> 00:30:28.452
They've been neighbors for three years.

413
00:30:28.618 --> 00:30:32.088
She'd never suspect them. and now
they're taking her straight to Carroll.

414
00:30:32.247 --> 00:30:36.252
He's finding people to help him do it
on the damn Internet.

415
00:30:36.418 --> 00:30:38.136
It's like they're his followers.

416
00:30:38.337 --> 00:30:40.590
I'm not buying two men
would pretend to be gay...

417
00:30:40.756 --> 00:30:43.851
...and shack up next to a woman
because some nut job told them to.

418
00:30:44.009 --> 00:30:47.604
The prison guard worships him.
Ice-pick lady is brainwashed...

419
00:30:47.763 --> 00:30:50.858
...to kill herself.
These two guys have dedicated...

420
00:30:51.016 --> 00:30:52.484
...years of their lives to him.

421
00:30:52.642 --> 00:30:56.237
There's a fanatical obsession
at play here. It's a cult.

422
00:31:00.025 --> 00:31:02.619
Nevermore. "The Raven."

423
00:31:02.778 --> 00:31:06.123
Poe is symbolizing the finality of death.

424
00:31:07.074 --> 00:31:09.372
Have you pulled the GPS?
Where are the satellites?

425
00:31:09.534 --> 00:31:11.207
- I knew you'd show up.
- Do something!

426
00:31:11.370 --> 00:31:12.963
How many check points are set up?

427
00:31:13.121 --> 00:31:14.418
- Get him out of here!
- Move!

428
00:31:14.581 --> 00:31:16.208
No! Hardy!

429
00:31:26.259 --> 00:31:28.261
[GRUNTS]

430
00:31:42.943 --> 00:31:45.321
ANNIE: Back off. dude.
RYAN: Sorry.

431
00:31:45.487 --> 00:31:46.989
ANNIE:
Come on. Sarah.

432
00:31:48.031 --> 00:31:49.578
SARAH:
You don't have to be rude.

433
00:31:49.741 --> 00:31:51.163
Sorry. sir.

434
00:31:53.829 --> 00:31:55.923
ANNIE: There's a killer.
you want me to have manners.

435
00:31:57.249 --> 00:32:00.753
- That was creepy.
SARAH: The whole night's been creepy.

436
00:32:01.962 --> 00:32:03.009
[DOOR CLOSED]

437
00:32:16.351 --> 00:32:18.353
[SARAH SCREAMING]

438
00:32:26.194 --> 00:32:28.196
[PANTING]

439
00:32:28.864 --> 00:32:30.116
SARAH:
Behind you.

440
00:32:30.699 --> 00:32:31.916
[RYAN GRUNTS]

441
00:32:32.075 --> 00:32:34.077
[CARROLL GRUNTS]

442
00:32:49.968 --> 00:32:51.720
[GUNSHOT]

443
00:33:19.080 --> 00:33:21.378
- Hey. what do you got?
- Both men were listed...

444
00:33:21.541 --> 00:33:24.670
-...in the prison's visitor log.
- You got a file on these guys?

445
00:33:24.836 --> 00:33:27.806
Nothing except for some property records
in Lake Whitehurst.

446
00:33:45.023 --> 00:33:46.775
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

447
00:34:04.543 --> 00:34:05.920
[TIRES SCREECH]

448
00:35:31.838 --> 00:35:33.590
I came alone. Joe.

449
00:35:33.923 --> 00:35:36.301
Isn't that what you wanted?

450
00:35:39.512 --> 00:35:41.560
SARAH:
No! No!

451
00:35:41.973 --> 00:35:43.941
No!

452
00:35:44.309 --> 00:35:46.983
No! No!

453
00:35:47.145 --> 00:35:49.694
No!

454
00:35:50.857 --> 00:35:51.904
[PANTING]

455
00:35:54.277 --> 00:35:56.655
SARAH:
No! No!

456
00:35:56.988 --> 00:36:00.117
No! No!

457
00:36:29.270 --> 00:36:30.943
Hello. Ryan.

458
00:36:33.566 --> 00:36:34.658
[GRUNTS]

459
00:36:37.946 --> 00:36:41.576
I was curious to see
how your heart was holding up.

460
00:36:44.619 --> 00:36:46.292
I see it has its limits.

461
00:36:46.454 --> 00:36:47.956
[RYAN PANTING]

462
00:36:53.670 --> 00:36:55.013
Where is she?

463
00:36:55.171 --> 00:37:00.052
You know. the human eye is connected
by seven muscles.

464
00:37:02.929 --> 00:37:04.852
I removed each one...

465
00:37:05.432 --> 00:37:07.184
...individually.

466
00:37:09.561 --> 00:37:11.359
You know how hard that is to do?

467
00:37:11.521 --> 00:37:14.491
SARAH: No! No! No!
- Sarah!

468
00:37:14.649 --> 00:37:15.696
[RECORDER BEEPS]

469
00:37:17.235 --> 00:37:18.282
[RECORDER BEEPS]

470
00:37:18.445 --> 00:37:20.789
<i>No! Ne!</i>

471
00:37:20.947 --> 00:37:24.292
You know how I love my little souvenirs.

472
00:37:24.451 --> 00:37:25.703
<i>No!</i>

473
00:37:26.327 --> 00:37:27.920
[GROANING]

474
00:37:31.750 --> 00:37:33.673
[RYAN SCREAMING]

475
00:37:38.548 --> 00:37:41.222
She lasted much longer
than I thought she would.

476
00:37:43.011 --> 00:37:44.763
She's quite the fighter.

477
00:37:47.891 --> 00:37:51.737
I'd like to turn myself in. I surrender.

478
00:37:51.895 --> 00:37:53.693
[RYAN GRUNTS]

479
00:37:53.855 --> 00:37:55.857
I surrender!

480
00:37:56.524 --> 00:37:58.572
Stop! Hardy!

481
00:37:59.611 --> 00:38:03.366
- I surrender!
- Come on. get off him! Get off him!

482
00:38:08.369 --> 00:38:09.746
I surrender!

483
00:38:09.913 --> 00:38:12.792
[RYAN GRUNTING]

484
00:38:29.516 --> 00:38:32.065
JENNIFER:
Carroll's en route to Richmond.

485
00:38:32.685 --> 00:38:35.404
He'll be placed in federal detention
until this is over.

486
00:38:37.982 --> 00:38:42.704
Eighteen months I worked the case.
Couldn't crack it.

487
00:38:47.951 --> 00:38:50.625
I made so many mistakes.

488
00:38:53.373 --> 00:38:55.216
But Sarah...

489
00:38:57.460 --> 00:38:59.053
...I saved her.

490
00:39:02.257 --> 00:39:03.600
How'd you know he'd be here?

491
00:39:04.384 --> 00:39:06.057
Carroll's book was inspired...

492
00:39:06.219 --> 00:39:09.564
...by Poe's last unfinished work.
"The Light-House."

493
00:39:10.014 --> 00:39:11.891
Sarah was his unfinished work.

494
00:39:13.768 --> 00:39:15.395
Yeah.

495
00:39:16.729 --> 00:39:19.232
He wanted to get the ending right.

496
00:39:30.952 --> 00:39:33.250
Joe Carroll had 47 dedicated websites.

497
00:39:33.413 --> 00:39:36.383
Over a thousand blogs.
chat rooms. online forums.

498
00:39:36.541 --> 00:39:42.264
- He could have multiple resources.
- Hardy. He'll only talk to you.

499
00:39:44.299 --> 00:39:45.926
[DOOR LOCK BUZZES
THEN DOOR OPENS]

500
00:40:08.156 --> 00:40:11.080
Sarah had to die. Ryan.

501
00:40:12.035 --> 00:40:16.381
I know it's sad. It's tragic. Poor thing.

502
00:40:17.332 --> 00:40:20.927
She worked very hard
to get her life back together.

503
00:40:21.544 --> 00:40:25.799
And she had done quite nicely.
which is more than I can say for some.

504
00:40:26.549 --> 00:40:30.349
You've been
quite the disappointment. Ryan.

505
00:40:30.762 --> 00:40:34.892
I never expected you capable
of In <i>Cold</i> Blood...

506
00:40:35.141 --> 00:40:37.894
...but what was it
with that true-crime drivel?

507
00:40:38.102 --> 00:40:42.653
So what's my sequel about. Joe?
Everyone outside is anxious to know.

508
00:40:43.483 --> 00:40:44.530
Hmm.

509
00:40:44.692 --> 00:40:45.909
Well...

510
00:40:46.778 --> 00:40:48.496
It's going to be a collaboration.

511
00:40:50.531 --> 00:40:52.533
We're going to write this together. Ryan.

512
00:40:53.117 --> 00:40:57.748
My first book
was clearly too avant-garde.

513
00:40:57.914 --> 00:41:01.009
Lost in literati pretense.

514
00:41:01.501 --> 00:41:06.723
My new story will play
to a much wider audience.

515
00:41:07.507 --> 00:41:08.884
[CARROLL CHUCKLES]

516
00:41:09.050 --> 00:41:12.145
Even Poe whored himself out eventually.

517
00:41:14.514 --> 00:41:18.314
So the prison guard. gay neighbors...

518
00:41:19.727 --> 00:41:23.072
How do they figure into your new plot?

519
00:41:24.482 --> 00:41:28.362
- We know about the cult.
- I'm not a big fan of that word.

520
00:41:28.528 --> 00:41:31.031
I like to think of them as my friends.

521
00:41:31.698 --> 00:41:35.453
It's important to have friends. Ryan.

522
00:41:36.369 --> 00:41:38.747
Did you know that the FBI estimates...

523
00:41:38.913 --> 00:41:44.920
...that up to 300 serial killers are active
in the U.S. on any given day?

524
00:41:48.589 --> 00:41:49.636
Oh.

525
00:41:49.799 --> 00:41:51.551
OFFICER:
Sorry. didn't mean to scare you.

526
00:41:51.718 --> 00:41:54.517
- Is everything okay?
- Extra patrol this evening.

527
00:41:54.679 --> 00:41:56.898
I thought they caught him.
I saw it on the news.

528
00:41:57.056 --> 00:41:59.434
Mind if I look around.
check your doors and windows?

529
00:41:59.600 --> 00:42:03.480
Do you have any friends. Ryan?

530
00:42:06.357 --> 00:42:08.906
Come on in. I think everyone's asleep.

531
00:42:14.782 --> 00:42:17.456
I will be your friend.

532
00:42:19.954 --> 00:42:22.924
Even though you slept with my wife.

533
00:42:23.249 --> 00:42:26.503
MAN [ON TV]: <i>There is breaking news
tonight from Waverly. Virginia...</i>

534
00:42:26.669 --> 00:42:29.673
<i>...where serial killer Joe Carroll
has finally been caught.</i>

535
00:42:29.839 --> 00:42:32.968
<i>The escaped convict was found
at an abandoned--</i>

536
00:42:34.177 --> 00:42:35.599
Did she show you the letter?

537
00:42:38.014 --> 00:42:40.312
What's he talking about?
What letter?

538
00:42:40.475 --> 00:42:45.732
Claire is very important. Ryan.
Every good story needs a love interest.

539
00:42:45.897 --> 00:42:48.741
- I'm going to bed. Good night.
- Good night.

540
00:42:51.277 --> 00:42:54.076
She's the only woman
I've ever truly loved.

541
00:42:55.031 --> 00:42:56.453
<i>CARROLL:
She's the mother of my son.</i>

542
00:42:56.616 --> 00:42:58.118
Joey?

543
00:43:00.787 --> 00:43:03.711
- And I'd like to see her.
- She'd never agree to that.

544
00:43:04.832 --> 00:43:07.551
She might just change her mind
about that.

545
00:43:07.752 --> 00:43:11.848
Joey? Joey? Where is he? Joey?

546
00:43:12.006 --> 00:43:14.259
<i>CARROLL: I thought I might go
more traditional this time.</i>

547
00:43:14.425 --> 00:43:17.929
Hero. villain. Good versus evil.
I need a strong protagonist...

548
00:43:18.096 --> 00:43:21.600
...so the reader can truly invest.

549
00:43:21.766 --> 00:43:26.522
A flawed. broken man
searching for redemption.

550
00:43:26.896 --> 00:43:32.744
That is you. You are my flawed hero.

551
00:43:32.902 --> 00:43:36.782
Yes. I ensured that by killing Sarah.

552
00:43:38.241 --> 00:43:41.962
She was the inciting incident.
The hero's call to action.

553
00:43:42.120 --> 00:43:44.543
This is merely the prologue.
just the beginning.

554
00:43:44.705 --> 00:43:49.006
That was the entire point
of Sarah's death.

555
00:43:51.087 --> 00:43:52.964
It was for you.

556
00:43:58.052 --> 00:44:01.306
If this book ends with anything
other than your death...

557
00:44:01.472 --> 00:44:03.349
...you better plan on a rewrite.

558
00:44:05.476 --> 00:44:08.229
[SCREAMING]
Guards! Guards! Guards!

559
00:44:08.396 --> 00:44:10.865
Joey. honey? Where are you?
Where's Denise?

560
00:44:11.023 --> 00:44:14.744
<i>Denise? Where is“? Where is Denise?</i>

561
00:44:14.902 --> 00:44:18.202
CARROLL: Guards!
- Don't move!

562
00:44:18.364 --> 00:44:21.038
Where's my son? Joey?

563
00:44:21.200 --> 00:44:23.248
<i>Joey. where are you?</i>

564
00:44:23.411 --> 00:44:26.460
Call Claire.
It's just the beginning.

565
00:44:30.084 --> 00:44:31.336
It's gonna be a classic.

566
00:44:33.796 --> 00:44:38.472
It'll be our masterpiece. Call Claire.

567
00:44:38.634 --> 00:44:40.762
Call Claire!

568
00:45:29.435 --> 00:45:31.437
[English - US - SDH]
